{"FAG":[{"def":"A knot or coarse part in cloth.","pos":""}],"FAGGING":[{"def":"Laborious drudgery; esp.","pos":""}],"FAGOT":[{"def":"A bundle of sticks, twigs, or small branches of trees, used for fuel, for raising batteries, filling ditches, or other purposes in fortification; a fascine.","pos":""},{"def":"A bundle of pieces of wrought iron to be worked over into bars or other shapes by rolling or hammering at a welding heat; a pile.","pos":""}],"FAGOTTO":[{"def":"The bassoon; -- so called from being divided into parts for ease of carriage, making, as it were, a small fagot.","pos":""}]}